{"type":"message","id":"b38bd798","parentId":"fd35f6d1","timestamp":"2026-02-28T06:36:12.421Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sat 2026-02-28 06:36 UTC] [Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: You are a Data Analyst. Your responsibilities:\n1. Analyze user behavior and metrics\n2. Create dashboards and visualizations\n3. SQL queries and data extraction\n4. Statistical analysis and reporting\n5. Data-driven insights and recommendations\n\nAlways respond as a Data Analyst - be analytical and provide actionable insights."}],"timestamp":1772260572418}}
{"type":"message","id":"be84575c","parentId":"b38bd798","timestamp":"2026-02-28T06:36:22.144Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is setting up a subagent context for a Data Analyst role. Let me understand what's happening:\n\n1. This appears to be a subagent session that was spawned\n2. The role is \"Data Analyst\" with specific responsibilities around data analysis, visualization, SQL, and insights\n3. The user hasn't asked me to do anything specific yet - they've just established the context\n\nSince this is a subagent context and no specific task has been given, I should acknowledge the role and wait for a specific task to analyze. The user is setting up my persona, so I should respond appropriately as a Data Analyst would.\n\nI should:\n1. Acknowledge the role setup\n2. Ask what data or analysis task they'd like me to work on\n3. Be ready to provide analytical, data-driven insights once a task is given","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"สวัสดีครับ! 🐣\n\n**Data Analyst Mode: Activated**\n\nReady to help with:\n- 📊 User behavior & metrics analysis\n- 📈 Dashboards & visualizations  \n- 🗄️ SQL queries & data extraction\n- 📉 Statistical analysis & reporting\n- 💡 Data-driven insights & recommendations\n\n**What would you like me to analyze?**\n\nPlease share:\n- Dataset location or sample data\n- Specific questions or hypotheses to investigate\n- Desired output format (dashboard, report, SQL queries, etc.)\n\nI'm standing by to dig into the data and deliver actionable insights! 📊✨"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"moonshot","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":5949,"output":300,"cacheRead":4608,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":10857,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772260572420}}
{"type":"message","id":"11164acb","parentId":"be84575c","timestamp":"2026-02-28T07:31:50.418Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sat 2026-02-28 07:18 UTC] วิเคราะห์ส่วน AI/ML ของระบบนี้:\n\n**AI-Powered Construction Intelligence Platform**\n\n**AI Components:**\n1. **Pre-Project AI** - Risk assessment model วิเคราะห์ก่อนรับงาน\n   - Historical project success prediction\n   - Client payment behavior analysis\n   - Material cost forecasting\n   - Labor availability prediction\n\n2. **During-Project AI** - Real-time monitoring\n   - Anomaly detection (cost overrun, schedule delay)\n   - Resource optimization (labor, material, equipment)\n   - Predictive maintenance for equipment\n   - Computer Vision for safety compliance\n\n3. **Post-Project AI** - ESG & Performance analysis\n   - Sentiment analysis from employee feedback\n   - Carbon footprint calculation\n   - Profitability analysis\n   - Benchmarking against industry standards\n\n**Data Sources:**\n- Historical project data\n- Real-time IoT sensors (optional)\n- External APIs (weather, material prices, SET data)\n- Employee feedback/surveys\n- CCTV footage (for computer vision)\n\nวิเคราะห์:\n1. ML Models ที่เหมาะสม (Regression, Classification, Time-series, NLP, CV)\n2. Data Pipeline architecture\n3. Training data requirements\n4. Model deployment strategy\n5. Performance metrics\n6. Potential challenges"}],"timestamp":1772263910416,"provenance":{"kind":"inter_session","sourceSessionKey":"agent:main:main","sourceChannel":"telegram","sourceTool":"sessions_send"}}}
{"type":"message","id":"c3b073bc","parentId":"11164acb","timestamp":"2026-02-28T07:33:37.140Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"ผู้ใช้ต้องการให้ฉันวิเคราะห์ส่วน AI/ML ของระบบ Construction Intelligence Platform นี้ ให้ละเอียดตาม 6 หัวข้อที่เสนอมา ฉันจะตอบเป็นภาษาไทยและให้รายละเอียดเชิงเทคนิคที่ครอบคลุม\n\nเนื้อหาที่ต้องครอบคลุม:\n1. ML Models ที่เหมาะสมสำหรับแต่ละ component\n2. Data Pipeline architecture\n3. Training data requirements\n4. Model deployment strategy\n5. Performance metrics\n6. Potential challenges\n\nฉันจะสร้างการวิเคราะห์ที่ครอบคลุมและเป็นระบบ โดยแบ่งตาม 3 ส่วนหลักของระบบ (Pre-Project, During-Project, Post-Project)","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"# 🤖 AI/ML Architecture Analysis: Construction Intelligence Platform\n\n## 📊 Executive Summary\n\nระบบนี้เป็น **Multi-Modal AI Platform** ที่ครอบคลุมทั้ง Predictive, Prescriptive และ Descriptive Analytics ครบวงจรตั้งแต่ Pre → During → Post Project\n\n---\n\n## 1️⃣ ML Models by Component\n\n### 🎯 **Pre-Project AI** (Decision Support)\n\n| Feature | ML Model | Algorithm/Approach | Justification |\n|---------|----------|-------------------|---------------|\n| **Project Success Prediction** | Classification | XGBoost/LightGBM + SHAP | Handle tabular data, feature importance สำคัญ |\n| **Client Payment Behavior** | Classification + Survival Analysis | Random Forest + Cox PH | ทำนาย default risk + time-to-payment |\n| **Material Cost Forecasting** | Time Series | Prophet / ARIMA / LSTM | Seasonality + trend capture |\n| **Labor Availability** | Regression + Classification | Gradient Boosting | ผสม numeric prediction + availability status |\n\n**Recommended Stack:**\n```python\n# Primary: XGBoost/LightGBM (structured data)\n# Secondary: Prophet (time series decomposition)\n# Ensembling: Stacking classifier for final decision\n```\n\n---\n\n### 🔄 **During-Project AI** (Real-time Operations)\n\n| Feature | ML Model | Algorithm/Approach | Latency Requirement |\n|---------|----------|-------------------|---------------------|\n| **Anomaly Detection** | Unsupervised + Supervised | Isolation Forest + LSTM Autoencoder | < 5 min (near real-time) |\n| **Resource Optimization** | Optimization + RL | Linear Programming + Deep Q-Network | Batch (hourly) |\n| **Predictive Maintenance** | Time Series + Classification | LSTM/GRU + Random Forest | < 15 min alert |\n| **Safety Compliance CV** | Computer Vision | YOLOv8/v9 + Pose Estimation (MediaPipe) | Real-time streaming |\n\n**Model Details:**\n```python\n# Anomaly Detection - Hybrid Approach\n# Layer 1: Isolation Forest (unsupervised - catch unknown patterns)\n# Layer 2: LSTM Autoencoder (sequence anomaly)\n# Layer 3: Rule-based threshold (business logic)\n\n# Safety CV Pipeline\n# YOLOv9 (object detection: hard hat, vest, harness)\n# MediaPipe/PoseNet (human pose - fall detection, unsafe posture)\n# OCR (safety sign compliance)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 📈 **Post-Project AI** (Analytics & Reporting)\n\n| Feature | ML Model | Algorithm/Approach | Output |\n|---------|----------|-------------------|--------|\n| **Sentiment Analysis** | NLP | Finetuned BERT/DeBERTa (Thai: WangchanBERTa) | Sentiment score + topic extraction |\n| **Carbon Footprint** | Regression + Calculation Engine | XGBoost + IPCC Standards | CO2e estimation |\n| **Profitability Analysis** | Regression | Multiple Linear Regression + GBM | Margin prediction |\n| **Benchmarking** | Clustering + Ranking | K-Means + Percentile Analysis | Industry percentile ranking |\n\n---\n\n## 2️⃣ Data Pipeline Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     DATA SOURCES LAYER                          │\n├─────────────┬─────────────┬─────────────┬─────────────┬─────────┤\n│  Historical │    IoT      │  External   │  Employee   │  CCTV   │\n│   Projects  │   Sensors   │    APIs     │  Feedback   │  Feeds  │\n└──────┬──────┴──────┬──────┴──────┬──────┴──────┬──────┴────┬────┘\n       │             │             │             │           │\n       ▼             ▼             ▼             ▼           ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                  INGESTION LAYER (Apache Kafka)                 │\n│  • Real-time streams (IoT, CCTV)                               │\n│  • Batch ingestion (historical, surveys)                        │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n                              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│              PROCESSING LAYER (Apache Spark / dbt)              │\n│  • Data cleaning & validation                                   │\n│  • Feature engineering                                          │\n│  • Enrichment (weather join, inflation adjustment)              │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n              ┌───────────────┼───────────────┐\n              ▼               ▼               ▼\n┌─────────────────┐ ┌─────────────────┐ ┌─────────────────┐\n│  FEATURE STORE  │ │   MODEL STORE   │ │  DATA WAREHOUSE │\n│  (Feast/Tecton) │ │   (MLflow)      │ │  (Snowflake/BQ) │\n│                 │ │                 │ │                 │\n│  • Versioned    │ │  • Model registry│ │  • Analytics    │\n│    features     │ │  • Experiments  │ │  • Reporting    │\n│  • Online/Offline│ │  • Artifacts   │ │  • BI dashboards│\n└────────┬────────┘ └────────┬────────┘ └─────────────────┘\n         │                   │\n         ▼                   ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│              SERVING LAYER (Multi-Modal)                        │\n├─────────────────┬─────────────────┬─────────────────────────────┤\n│  Real-time API  │  Batch Inference │  Edge Deployment            │\n│  (FastAPI/KServe)│ (Airflow/Dagster)│ (NVIDIA Jetson/AWS Greengrass)\n│                 │                 │                             │\n│  • /predict     │  • Hourly jobs  │  • On-site CV inference     │\n│  • /anomaly     │  • Daily ETL    │  • Offline capability       │\n└─────────────────┴─────────────────┴─────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3️⃣ Training Data Requirements\n\n### 📊 **Volume Estimates**\n\n| Model Category | Minimum Records | Optimal Records | Data Freshness |\n|---------------|-----------------|-----------------|----------------|\n| Project Success | 500+ projects | 5,000+ projects | 2-year sliding |\n| Payment Behavior | 1,000+ clients | 10,000+ invoices | Real-time |\n| Cost Forecasting | 3 years daily | 10 years daily | Daily update |\n| Anomaly Detection | 6 months IoT | 2 years IoT | Real-time |\n| Safety CV | 10,000 images | 100,000+ images | Quarterly retrain |\n| Sentiment NLP | 5,000 reviews | 50,000+ reviews | Monthly retrain |\n\n### 🏗️ **Data Schema Requirements**\n\n```sql\n-- Core Project Table (Pre-Project Features)\nCREATE TABLE project_features (\n    project_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,\n    client_id UUID,\n    project_type ENUM('residential', 'commercial', 'industrial'),\n    contract_value DECIMAL(15,2),\n    project_duration_days INT,\n    location_province VARCHAR(50),\n    complexity_score FLOAT,  -- engineered feature\n    historical_client_payment_rate FLOAT,\n    market_material_volatility FLOAT,\n    seasonal_factor FLOAT,\n    -- Target variables\n    actual_profit_margin FLOAT,\n    was_delayed BOOLEAN,\n    client_defaulted BOOLEAN\n);\n\n-- IoT Sensor Table (During-Project)\nCREATE TABLE iot_readings (\n    timestamp TIMESTAMP,\n    equipment_id UUID,\n    project_id UUID,\n    temperature FLOAT,\n    vibration FLOAT,\n    fuel_consumption FLOAT,\n    operating_hours FLOAT,\n    gps_location GEOGRAPHY,\n    -- Anomaly labels (for supervised training)\n    is_breakdown BOOLEAN,\n    maintenance_type VARCHAR(50)\n);\n\n-- Safety CV Training Data\nCREATE TABLE safety_labels (\n    image_id UUID,\n    image_url VARCHAR(500),\n    bounding_boxes JSON,  -- COCO format\n    keypoints JSON,       -- Pose keypoints\n    violations JSON,      -- ['no_helmet', 'no_vest']\n    labeled_by VARCHAR(50),\n    label_confidence FLOAT\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4️⃣ Model Deployment Strategy\n\n### 🚀 **Deployment Architecture**\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     PRODUCTION ENVIRONMENT                    │\n├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  ┌─────────────┐    ┌─────────────┐    ┌─────────────┐      │\n│  │   Model A   │    │   Model B   │    │   Model C   │      │\n│  │  (Pre-Proj) │    │ (During-Pr) │    │  (Post-Pr)  │      │\n│  │             │    │             │    │             │      │\n│  │  Container  │    │  Container  │    │  Container  │      │\n│  │  (Docker)   │    │  (Docker)   │    │  (Docker)   │      │\n│  └──────┬──────┘    └──────┬──────┘    └──────┬──────┘      │\n│         │                   │                   │             │\n│         └───────────────────┼───────────────────┘             │\n│                             ▼                                │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │\n│  │            Kubernetes / ECS (Orchestration)          │     │\n│  │  • Auto-scaling (HPA based on CPU/RPS)               │     │\n│  │  • Rolling updates (zero-downtime)                   │     │\n│  │  • Circuit breaker patterns                          │     │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │\n│                             │                                │\n│                             ▼                                │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │\n│  │              API Gateway (Kong/AWS API GW)           │     │\n│  │  • Rate limiting • Auth • Request routing            │     │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 🔄 **MLOps Pipeline**\n\n```yaml\n# CI/CD for ML (GitOps approach)\nCI Pipeline:\n  1. Data validation (Great Expectations)\n  2. Unit tests (pytest)\n  3. Model training (experiment tracking in MLflow)\n  4. Model evaluation (A/B test framework)\n  5. Model promotion (registry staging → production)\n\nCD Pipeline:\n  1. Build container image\n  2. Security scan (Trivy/Snyk)\n  3. Deploy to staging\n  4. Integration tests\n  5. Canary deployment (10% → 50% → 100%)\n  6. Rollback capability\n```\n\n### 🖥️ **Edge Deployment (Safety CV)**\n\n```\nOn-Site Hardware: NVIDIA Jetson AGX Orin / Intel NUC + GPU\n├── Model: TensorRT-optimized YOLO (FP16 quantization)\n├── Latency: < 100ms per frame\n├── Bandwidth: Only alerts + metadata to cloud\n└── Fallback: Local rule-based system if AI offline\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5️⃣ Performance Metrics\n\n### 📏 **ML Model Metrics**\n\n| Model | Primary Metric | Target | Secondary Metrics |\n|-------|---------------|--------|-------------------|\n| **Project Success** | F1-Score | > 0.75 | Precision, Recall, AUC-ROC |\n| **Payment Default** | Precision@Top20% | > 0.80 | Recall, Calibration error |\n| **Cost Forecast** | MAPE | < 15% | RMSE, MAE, Directional accuracy |\n| **Anomaly Detection** | F1-Score | > 0.70 | Precision, Recall, False positive rate |\n| **Predictive Maintenance** | F2-Score | > 0.75 | Time-to-failure MAE |\n| **Safety CV** | mAP@0.5 | > 0.85 | FPS, False negative rate |\n| **Sentiment NLP** | F1-Score | > 0.80 | Accuracy per class |\n\n### 🏢 **Business Metrics**\n\n```python\n# Pre-Project Impact\nROI_improvement = (Post_AI_win_rate - Baseline_win_rate) / Baseline_win_rate\nBad_debt_reduction = (Baseline_default_rate - Post_AI_default_rate)\n\n# During-Project Impact  \nCost_savings = Predicted_vs_actual_variance_reduction\nSafety_improvement = (Accidents_per_1M_hours_baseline - Current) / Baseline\n\n# Post-Project Impact\nESG_score_improvement = Carbon_tracking_accuracy\nEmployee_retention_correlation = Sentiment_score_vs_turnover\n```\n\n### 📊 **Monitoring Dashboard**\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    ML SYSTEM MONITORING                      │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  Data Drift     │  Concept Drift  │  Model Performance      │\n│  ├─ KS test     │  ├─ PSI score   │  ├─ Accuracy degradation│\n│  ├─ PSI > 0.2   │  ├─ AUC drop    │  ├─ Latency p99         │\n│  └─ Feature stats│ └─ Retraining  │  └─ Throughput RPS      │\n│                trigger                                       │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  Alerts: Slack/PagerDuty │  Auto-retraining: Enabled        │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6️⃣ Potential Challenges & Mitigations\n\n### ⚠️ **Challenge Matrix**\n\n| Risk Level | Challenge | Impact | Mitigation Strategy |\n|-----------|-----------|--------|---------------------|\n| 🔴 **HIGH** | **Data Sparsity** (New company, limited history) | Model underperformance | • Transfer learning from public datasets<br>• Bayesian approaches with priors<br>• Simulation/synthetic data |\n| 🔴 **HIGH** | **Concept Drift** (Economic changes, COVID, inflation) | Prediction degradation | • Continuous monitoring (Evidently/WhyLabs)<br>• Automated retraining triggers<br>• Ensemble with recent-only models |\n| 🟡 **MED** | **Class Imbalance** (Few accidents, rare defaults) | Poor recall on rare events | • SMOTE/ADASYN oversampling<br>• Cost-sensitive learning<br>• Anomaly detection for rare events |\n| 🟡 **MED** | **Multilingual NLP** (Thai + English feedback) | Sentiment accuracy | • WangchanBERTa (Thai-specific)<br>• Language detection + routing<br>• Multilingual models (mBERT/XLM-R) |\n| 🟡 **MED** | **Real-time CV Latency** | Safety alerts delayed | • Edge optimization (TensorRT/ONNX)<br>• Model quantization (INT8)<br>• Hardware acceleration |\n| 🟢 **LOW** | **Data Privacy** (Employee data, CCTV) | Compliance risk | • PII masking/redaction<br>• Consent management<br>• On-premise deployment option |\n| 🟢 **LOW** | **Model Interpretability** | Stakeholder trust | • SHAP/LIME explanations<br>• Feature importance dashboard<br>• Rule-based fallback |\n\n### 🛡️ **Risk Mitigation Architecture**\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    GOVERNANCE LAYER                         │\n│  • Model Cards (documentation)                              │\n│  • Bias detection (Fairlearn/AIF360)                        │\n│  • Explainability API (SHAP values)                         │\n│  • Audit trails (MLflow tracking)                           │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n                              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    SAFETY MECHANISMS                        │\n│  • Human-in-the-loop for high-stakes decisions              │\n│  • Confidence thresholding (low confidence → escalate)       │\n│  • Shadow mode deployment (log predictions, don't act)      │\n│  • Circuit breakers (failover to rule-based)                │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## 🎯 Implementation Roadmap\n\n### Phase 1: Foundation (Months 1-2)\n- [ ] Data warehouse setup + ETL pipelines\n- [ ] Feature store implementation\n- [ ] Baseline models (simple heuristics)\n\n### Phase 2: Core ML (Months 3-4)\n- [ ] Pre-Project AI models (XGBoost baselines)\n- [ ] Cost forecasting (Prophet)\n- [ ] Basic anomaly detection (Isolation Forest)\n\n### Phase 3: Advanced AI (Months 5-6)\n- [ ] Safety CV deployment (YOLO edge)\n- [ ] NLP sentiment pipeline\n- [ ] Real-time optimization (RL)\n\n### Phase 4: Production Hardening (Month 7+)\n- [ ] MLOps automation\n- [ ] A/B testing framework\n- [ ] Advanced monitoring\n\n---\n\n## 📋 Key Recommendations\n\n1. **Start Simple**: XGBoost + Prophet ให้ผลดีกับ structured data มากกว่า Deep Learning ในช่วงแรก\n2. **Invest in Data Quality**: Garbage in = Garbage out โดยเฉพาะ historical project data\n3. **Edge First for CV**: Safety detection ต้อง real-time → ลงทุน edge hardware\n4. **Human-in-the-Loop**: อย่า auto-approve 100% โดยเฉพาะ high-value decisions\n5. **Thai NLP**: ใช้ WangchanBERTa หรือ typhoon สำหรับ sentiment ภาษาไทย\n\n---\n\n**สรุป**: ระบบนี้เป็น **Enterprise-grade AI Platform** ที่มีศักยภาพสูง แต่ต้องลงทุนใน data infrastructure และ MLOps ให้ดี ควรเริ่มจาก use case ที่มี data พร้อม (เช่น cost forecasting) แล้วค่อยๆ expand ไปส่วนที่ซับซ้อนขึ้น 🏗️🤖"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"moonshot","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":5886,"output":4168,"cacheRead":4608,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14662,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772263910418}}
